        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "John Phillips, a retired music teacher who still plays with the Vallejo Symphony Orchestra, has a great attitude about the situation. “Everything can be replaced,” he told local journalists. There’s nothing to be done with what’s been lost at this point, so the man is right. Although it’s reported he’s especially sad the Riley was lost. It had been his father’s car until he passed away in 2011. The Morris Minor was driven to and from work by Phillip’s father.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "His wife, Patty, was home alone when the power went out at 1:30 in the morning. She opened the front door to see what was happening and felt a “blast of hot air.” An official told her to evacuate and so she grabbed what she could. Unfortunately, driving one of those classic cars to safety wasn’t part of the plan.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "A fundraiser has been started to help the couple recover from the catastrophic loss.",
